 to Middle school up to class7. After [[Indian independence]], Kutri villagers used to go nearby school for high school education i.e. BK Sahoo High School at [[Warisaliganj]].  In 1970\u2019s there were urgent need felt by villagers to improve educational institution in the village for higher secondary education and it was finally decided in Oct 1972 during [[Durga Puja]] Festival that a high school is urgently needed in the proximity of the village. This need was further strengthened with demand of  improving literacy & education among girls. For girls, it was difficult to get higher education due to unavailability of high school in near by locations. At that time, President Late Bhishundeo Singh, Secretary Late Girijanandan Sharma, Treasurer Late Sunder Sharma, Auditor Parasnath Singh formed a committee with some nominated members Such as Sh. Umesh Chandra Sinha, Sh. Ram Lakhan Sharma, Sh. Kushewshar Singh, Late Bharat Singh, Late Rajpati Singh, Late Ramchandra Singh (Chaubhaiya) became active members for high school establishment. Role of president & secretary were immense to get land for the School and subscription or donation amount was offered by all members and many villagers. Considering education an urgent need, members of Natya Kala Parishad, Kutri initiated school foundation for higher education in the south of the village and a foundation stone of  high school was kept by the first district Magistrate of Nawada Shri Narendra Pal Singh on 5th Feb 1973 on the eve of Saraswati Puja. Surprisingly, 5th Feb was the birthday of Sh. Narendrapal Singh (then DM) and when invitation for foundation stone of school was given by Sh. Ram Lakhan Sharma, he accepted this request happily and was ready to support this noble work in all the way. Late Kushewshar Singh became the first Headmaster of Kutri high school and some unemployed villagers at that time used to teach there. Successor headmaster late Ram Naresh Singh put great effort to get uphill task of permanent high school approval from the government authority. In doing so Late Bandi Shankar Singh ([[MLA]], [[Warisaliganj]]), the son of first Chief minister of [[Bihar]] supported very well. In Dec. 1978, Kutri High school became govt approved high school now it is inter high school (10+2). Apart from, this, there was some coaching classes was run privately to bring better education in the village.  The unforgettable name of Late Haridwar Singh was one of them who privately run coaching cum school at late Shyam nandan Pathak banglow. He was very disciplined teacher and kept strong foundation of English literature & Mathematics in the students.  At present there is one middle school & one inter high school in our village where students from nearby villages even from Naromurar, Gorapar, Lohrajpur, Paingari etc. are coming for the education along with our village students. Thus we can say, that our forefathers had strategic vision towards education.\nIn late 1990,s & early 2000\u2019s, a group of villagers Dr. Amit Kumar, Prof.(Dr.) Baliram Pd Singh & Sh  Baliram Sharma understood the difficulties of students to get job oriented education and collected Rs 1100 (rupees eleven hundred only) each to initiate refresher classes for the students with the participation of learned & responsible villagers, such as late Jata Shankar Pathak Ji and many unemployed villagers at that time used to take classes to strengthen basics and to motivate students to face tough competition. Once again in 2020\u2019s Villagers who are in the job and business but out of village at present once again felt the need of the education, and thought that talent is everywhere and we need to up bring them through motivation & creating quiz & competition classes amongst students  to nourish them self dependant citizen of the country. In this direction, a [[WhatsApp]] group i.e. Kutri Residents Group initiated spread of education thought with the support of Maa kali Sewa Sansthan Kutri (Maa Kali Sewa Siksha Sansthan) and conducted [[Quiz]] competition amongst student of different classes to bring competition  amongst students and to understand importance of education under the shadow of Mr. Rupesh Kumar, Umakant, Anjani Kumar, Daya Shankar  who dedicated himself as educationists & motivators from their busy schedule to make it successful. From WhatsApp group, Dr. Amit Kumar. Rakesh Kumar, Mukesh Kumar Singh, Rupesh Kumar, Umakant, Prof. Baliram, sanjeev, Sonu etc took lead to move forward this education awareness under the supervision of Maa Kali Sewa Sanstahan President Shri Ram Avtar Sharma, Secretary, Shri Ram Lakhan Sharma & Treasurer Shri Rajendra Singh. Some of the villagers also contributed financially to support this initiative. MAA KALI SEWA SANSTHAN took active participation in opening saving account and contributed morally as well as financially to uplift poor students.\n\n==See also==\n* [[Villages in Bihar]] \n* [[Nawada District]]\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{cite web|url=http://nawada.nic.in |title=Official District Website |publisher= |date= |accessdate=}}\n\n[[Category:Villages in Nawada district]]\n", "text_old": "{{Cleanup|reason=reorganise image|date=March 2020}}\n{{Infobox settlement\n| name                    =Kutri \n| other_name              = \u0915\u0941\u091f\u0930\u0940\n| settlement_type         = Village \n| pushpin_map             = India Bihar#India\n| pushpin_label_position  = left\n| subdivision_type        = Country\n| subdivision_name        = {{flag|India}}\n| subdivision_type1       = [[States and territories of India|State]]\n| subdivision_name1       = [[Bihar]]\n| subdivision_type2       = [[List of regions of India|Region]]\n| subdivision_type3       = [[List of districts of India|District]]\n| subdivision_name3       = [[Nawada district|Nawada]]\n| government_type         = [[Panchayati raj (India)]]\n| governing_body          = [[Gram panchayat]] \n| pushpin_map_caption     = Location in Bihar, India\n| coordinates             = {{coord|25.023060|N|85.602250|E|display=inline,title}}\n| population_total        = 5445<ref name=\"auto\">{{cite web|url=http://censusindia.gov.in/2011census/dchb/1035_PART_B_DCHB_NAWADA.pdf |title= Nawada District Census Handbook Page No. 3 for Population and Page No. 76 for Village Code |publisher= |date= |accessdate=}}</ref>\n| population_as_of        = 2011\n| population_density_km2  = auto\n| demographics_type1      = Languages\n| demographics1_title1    = Official\n| demographics1_info1     = [[Hindi language|Hindi]]\n| timezone1               = [[Indian Standard Time|IST]]\n| utc_offset1             = +5:30\n| postal_code_type        = Postal Index Number \n| postal_code             = 805130<ref>{{cite web|url=https://nawada.nic.in/std-pin-codes/ |title= Postal Code (PIN) and STD Code |publisher= |date= |accessdate=}}</ref>\n| area_code_type          = Telephone code\n| area_code               = 06325<ref>{{cite web|url=https://nawada.nic.in/std-pin-codes/ |title= Postal Code (PIN) and STD Code |publisher= |date= |accessdate=}}</ref>\n| registration_plate      = BR-27-XXXX\n| website                 = {{URL|nawada.nic.in}}\n| footnotes               = \n}}\n[[Kutri]] Village with Census of [[India]] Village-code 257586 is located in [[Warisaliganj]] Block of [[Nawada district]] in [[Bihar]], [[India]]. It is one of the historical village amongst 80 villages of [[Warisaliganj]] Block of [[Nawada district]]. According to the government records, Kutri village has 842 houses spread in geographical areas of 368 hectares. It is situated 5 km away from [[Warisaliganj]] Block and 22km away from [[Nawada]]. As of 2009, Kutri village is also a [[gram Panchayat]]. <ref>{{cite web|url=https://nawada.nic.in/village-panchayats/ |title= Details of Blocks and Villages of Nawada District |publisher= |date= |accessdate=}}</ref> <ref name=\"auto\"/>\n\n==Kutri Gram Panchayat== \n<ref>{{cite web|url=https://cdn.s3waas.gov.in/s3a4f23670e1833f3fdb077ca70bbd5d66/uploads/2018/03/2018030651.pdf |title= Panchayat and Village Details of Nawada|publisher= |date= |accessdate=}}</ref>\nKutri Panchayat consists of following villages:\n*'''Kutri'''\n**[[Naromurar]]\n**Khirbhojna\n**Rampur\n\nKutri village has 3 sub villages, [[Naromurar]], Khirbhojna, Rampur, Tullapur, & Masankhama. Kutri & [[Naromurar]] inhabitants are [[Bhumihar]] [[Brahmins]] and [[Maithil Brahmins]].{{cn|date=March 2020}}\n\n[[File:Kutri Village Panorma View.jpg|thumb|center|Panorama View of Kutri.]]\n\n{{Gallery\n|title=Village Glimpses\n|align=center\n|File:Gardening near pond.jpg\n |alt1=Gardening Near Pond\n |Gardening Near Pond\n|File:Pond scene.jpg\n |alt2=Pond Beautification\n |Pond Beautification\n|File:Pond Glimpse.jpg\n |alt3=Distant view of Shivala at Pond\n |Distant view of Shivala at Pond\n|File:Pond Photo.jpg\n |alt4=Pond Glimpse\n |Pond Glimpse\n}}\n\n==Culture==\n\n[[File:Kusti.jpg |thumb|center|Kushti at Kutri.]]\n[[File:Kutri Kusti.jpg |thumb|center|Kushti at Kutri.]]\n\n{{Gallery\n|title=Cultural depictions of Kutri Village\n|align=center\n|File:Kusti photo1.jpg\n |alt1=Kushti Viewers\n |Kushti Viewers\n|File:Photo -kusti.jpg\n |alt2=Glimpse of viewers\n |Glimpse of viewers\n|File:Dangal View.jpg\n |alt3=Delighted spectators at Kushti\n |Delighted spectators at Kushti\n}}\n\n\n\n\n===Language===\nThe primary language used in Kutri is [[Magahi language|Magahi]] and [[Hindi language|Hindi]] as in the [[Nawada District]] and [[Magadh Division]] of [[Bihar]]<ref>{{cite web|url=https://books.google.co.in/books?id=sl_dDVctycgC&pg=PA481&dq=angika+in+west+bengal&redir_esc=y&hl=en#v=onepage&q=magahi&f=false |title= International Encyclopedia of Linguistics: 4-Volume Set By William Frawley |publisher= |date= |accessdate=}}</ref>\n\n\n{{Gallery\n|title=Temples of Kutri Village\n|align=center\n|File:Kali mata Mandir-Kutri-Nawada.jpg\n |alt1=Kali Mata Photo of Kutri Kali Mandir\n |Kali Mata Photo of Kutri Kali Mandir\n|File:Kali Mandir Under Construction.jpg\n |alt2=Kali Mandir (Under Construction) at Kutri\n |Kali Mandir (Under Construction) at Kutri\n|File:Kutri Kali Mandir construction update Feb2020.jpg\n |alt3=Kutri Kali  Mandir construction update Feb2020\n |Kutri Kali  Mandir construction update Feb2020\n|File:Shivala.jpg\n |alt4=Shivalaya temple North\n |Shivalaya temple North\n|File:Shivalaya full view.jpg\n |alt5=Shivala North\n |Shivala North\n|File:Shiva Gate.jpg\n |alt6=Shivala entry Gate\n |Shivala entry Gate\n|File:Shivala side view.jpg\n |alt7=Shivala lateral View\n |Shivala lateral View\n|File:Shivala rear view.jpg\n |alt8=Shivala rear view\n |Shivala rear view\n|File:Shivala1.jpg\n |alt9=Shivala Front View\n |Shivala Front View\n|File:Shiva Mandir at Kutri- Nawada.jpg\n |alt10=Shiva Mandir near the pond at Kutri\n |Shiva Mandir near the pond at Kutri\n|File:Shiva Temple pond Kutri.jpg\n |alt11=Distant view of Shivala at Pond\n |Distant view of Shivala at Pond\n|File:LaxmiNarayan Mandir.jpg\n |alt12=Laxmi Narayan Mandir at Kutri\n |Laxmi Narayan Mandir at Kutri\n}}\n\n==Geography==\n\n===Climate===\n\nThe table below shows historical monthly averages for climate variables in Kutri.\n{{Clear}}\n{{Weather box|collapsed =\n|location = [[Patna Airport]] (1981\u20132010, extremes 1951\u20132012)\n| metric first = Yes\n| single line = Yes\n| Jan record high C = 30.0\n| Feb record high C = 35.1\n| Mar record high C = 41.4\n| Apr record high C = 44.6\n| May record high C = 45.6\n| Jun record high C = 46.6\n| Jul record high C = 41.2\n| Aug record high C = 39.7\n| Sep record high C = 37.5\n| Oct record high C = 37.2\n| Nov record high C = 34.1\n| Dec record high C = 30.5\n| year record high C = 46.6\n| Jan high C = 22.4\n| Feb high C = 26.0\n| Mar high C = 32.2\n| Apr high C = 37.0\n| May high C = 37.4\n| Jun high C = 36.4\n| Jul high C = 33.0\n| Aug high C = 32.9\n| Sep high C = 32.5\n| Oct high C = 31.9\n| Nov high C = 29.0\n| Dec high C = 24.5\n| year high C = 31.3\n| Jan low C = 9.3\n| Feb low C 